Decapeptyl (triptorelin) in the treatment of endometriosis genitalis externa. The study involved 69 patients in whom endometriosis was diagnosed. The patients were divided into three groups randomly. In each of the groups, a different method of treatment was applied. In group A thermocoagulation was used, in group B triptorelin was used and in group C the above monitored methods of treatment were applied. Combined therapy involving the use of both thermocoagulation and triptorelin seen to be the most effective.